JPMorgan Chase & Co. story click {1<GO>} or {EXT2 <GO>}.  By Dawn Kopecki, Michael J. Moore and Christine Harper  May 11 (Bloomberg) -- JPMorgan Chase & Co.  Chief Executive
Officer  Jamie Dimon  said the firm suffered a $2 billion trading
loss after an “egregious” failure in a unit managing risks,
jeopardizing Wall Street banks’ efforts to loosen a federal ban
on bets with their own money.  To contact the editor responsible for this slideshow:
